==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anaërobic
<hw>An*a`⟦eum⟧*rob"ic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>an-</ets>not + <ets>a⟦eum⟧robic</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Not requiring air or oxygen for life; -- applied
especially to those microbes to which free oxygen is unnecessary;
ana⟦eum⟧robiotic; -- opposed to <ant>a⟦eum⟧robic</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Relating to, or like,
ana⟦eum⟧robies; ana⟦eum⟧robiotic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anaerobies</ent>⟦br⟧
